# 🛡️ How Websites Work – TryHackMe Notes

**📅 Date Completed:** June 23, 2025  
**🔗 TryHackMe Profile:** https://tryhackme.com/p/Tbach  
**💼 Path/Module:** Pre-security - How the Web Works

---

## 📚 Room Summary
  This room explained how a website is built using HTML and JavaScript, and what each language does for the website.
How the Front end the browser makes a request to the website and back end means the server processes you request and returns a response.
For the pratical part of this room the user went to a external website and made edits to both HTML and Javascript, had a lab that show the danger
of sensative data being forgotten about and show the user how to do a HTML injection yourself.

---

## 🧠 Key Concepts Learned
- How HTML (HyperText Markup Language) is the language to create website structure and content
- JavaScript is the language that builds the website functionality
- The differnce between Front end and Back end
- How sensative data exposure can lead to attacks
- Explains how a attacker can use a HTML injection on sensative data exposure

---

## 🛠️ Tools / Commands Used
- HTML editor
- JavaScript editor
- Sensitive Data exposer
- HTML injections
